@DATABASE "Itidy"
@INDEX MAIN

@NODE MAIN "iTidy v2.0"
@NEXT REQUIREMENTS

@{APEN 2}@{B}iTidy v2.0@{UB}@{APEN 1}
==========

@{B}A Workbench Icon and Window Tidy Tool for AmigaOS 3.2+@{UB}

Workbench drawers have a way of drifting into chaos over time, especially
after big Aminet extractions, cover disks, or years of "I will sort it
later" installs.

iTidy is a small utility I wrote to bring things back into shape. Point it
at a folder or an entire volume and it will tidy icon layouts and drawer
windows in a consistent, repeatable way, with optional recursion through
subfolders.

Version 2.0 adds a Workbench 3.2 ReAction GUI plus DefIcons-based icon
creation, so files without icons can be handled automatically. Where
supported, it can also generate thumbnail-style icons for images. Backups
are available so you can roll back a run if you change your mind.

